        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 2:19PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 219 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Providence, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
Providence...
Gatewood...
Blanch...
and Hamer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
